Ericsson Seeks Fair Play on Smartphone Patents, FTD Reports

-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 
2011-10-05T05:36:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/ericsson-seeks-fair-play-on-smartphone-patents-ftd-reports.html
Ericsson AB is pushing for fair play
among competitors on smartphone patents,  Financial Times
Deutschland  reported, citing Kasim Alfalahi, the company’s chief
intellectual property officer.  “No one owns all necessary rights in the mobile phone
industry,” the newspaper quoted the executive as saying in an
article published today. The number of patent disputes within
the industry will keep growing, according to Alfalahi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andreas Cremer in Berlin at 
 acremer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
